<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="506" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,815,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,959,985]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length 14.3–14.8; total width 7.7–8.0; head length 1.4–1.5; head width 3.2–3,4; interocular distance: 1.6–1.8; length of antenomeres I: 0.9–1.0; II: 1.0–1.1; III: 1.5; IV: 3.1–3.2; V: 3.6; pronotum length 2.7– 3.0; pronotum width 8.9–9.2; scutellum length 6.5–6.7; scutellum width 5.0–5.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,815,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1066,1092]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Diagnose.</emphasis>
Antennomeres with increasing lengths progressively (I&lt;II&lt;III&lt;IV&lt;V). Anterolateral margin of pronotum not punctured (
<figureCitation box="[441,545,1103,1129]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). Corium reddish brown (
<figureCitation box="[839,943,1103,1129]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process with arms of anterior bifurcation receiving 2/3 of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation box="[720,825,1139,1165]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Pseudosutures of abdomen with adjacent dark green spot (
<figureCitation box="[212,314,1175,1201]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[333,507,1174,1201]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface with spot restricted to coarse area of the pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1344,1175,1201]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[304,397,1211,1237]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); lateral expansions slightly globose and almost level with posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,1211,1237]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Superior process of the genital cup subtriangular, small and swollen (
<figureCitation box="[915,1002,1247,1273]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Paramere with head slightly concave; anterior and posterior lobe subtriangular; anterior lobe large with external face striated and reaching superior process of the genital cup; posterior lobe smaller than the anterior lobe and laterally directed (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1200,1319,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger shallowly excavated laterally, excavation covered by long and dense setae; posterior face elliptical (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1244,1355,1381]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Inner wall with small swollen area contiguous to posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[761,842,1391,1417]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[250,1339,204,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[199,1389,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genital capsule in posterolateral view, swollen area on inner wall of the pygophore indicated by the arrow: A—Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911526/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
, black arrow). Ventral rim in widely opened V-shaped with expansions hardly visible (
<figureCitation box="[519,611,1427,1453]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[634,833,1426,1453]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[852,943,1427,1453]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[171,1432,202,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypoxys striatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911507/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers VIII with distal margin slightly arched; outer and inner angles of the posterior margin rounded; mediolateral crest slightly swollen (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1363,1463,1489]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[247,1354,212,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-25@14.[199,1389,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female genital plates in oblique view, mediolateral crest swollen on valvifers VIII indicated by the arrow: A— Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911528/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
, black arrow); mesial borders with excavation narrow, deep and U-shaped. Valvulae IX clearly exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
